               <p>Bermuda, 1828.</p>
               <p>SISTER - I now take an opportunity of writing - lines to you, hoping they will - you in good health as they leave - at present. I have been very ill for - time, and have been in the Navy-hospital for five weeks, but am now - recovered, and expect to arrive at - mouth in a little time, as we are prep - to put to sea. I will let you know - I arrive there, as I shall want some help - my trunks home as they are loaded - xes, specimens of rock, and all sorts of - dsome shells; so no more at present.</p>
               <p>I remain your affectionate brother,</p>
